Winter 2017 Cohort

The following information and diagrams were compiled from the NICHE Year 1 Implementation Survey. The data represent responses submitted by NICHE Coordinators in the same Leadership Training Program (LTP) Cohort. Individual responses have been de-identified to maintain anonymity.

NICHE Program Leaders

Ninety two percent of the NICHE Coordinators of this LTP Cohort are female and 8 percent are male. On average, the NICHE Coordinators are 50 years of age and graduated between 1974 and 2010 with a Baccalaureate Degree as their first nursing degree. Eight percent have earned a master’s degree. Eight percent of the NICHE Coordinators are certified by the American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC) in gerontology and eight percent served as Geriatric Resource Nurses prior to becoming a NICHE Coordinator. Seventeen percent are Advanced Practice Nurses with most prepared as a Clinical Nurse Specialist (CNS) — Gerontological Focus. Forty two percent hold specialty certifications for Registered Nurses. The most common certifications held by the NICHE Coordinators of this cohort are: 1) Critical Care Nursing; 2) Critical Care Nursing,Nurse Executive—Advanced; and 3) Medical-Surgical Nursing. Eighty three percent are members of hospital-wide committees responsible for clinical practice and policy development and eighty three percent are members of hospital-wide committees responsible for improving the quality of care for older adults.
